---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="IoTera"
  description="IoTera gives facility teams a clearer way to watch utility usage across buildings, meters, and operating environments."
>
  <header class="site-header">
    <img src="/iotera-logo.png" alt="IoTera" />
    <nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Primary">
      <a href="#overview">Overview</a>
      <a href="#status">Status</a>
      <a href="https://app.iotera.asia">App</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <section class="hero" id="overview">
    <div class="panel hero-copy">
      <div class="eyebrow">Utility visibility for modern properties</div>
      <h1>Monitor meter data without the spreadsheet sprawl.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        IoTera is a property-focused monitoring platform for facilities that need
        a cleaner view of utility activity across sites, devices, and operating
        conditions. This is a temporary landing page scaffold for the marketing
        site and infrastructure setup.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="https://app.iotera.asia">Open app</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="mailto:hello@iotera.asia">Contact</a>
      </div>
      <div class="stats">
        <div class="stat">
          <strong>Astro</strong>
          <span>Static-site foundation ready for Netlify deployment.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <strong>Cloudflare</strong>
          <span>Planned DNS authority with separate app, API, and MQTT hosts.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <strong>IoTera</strong>
          <span>Brand assets and favicon baseline copied from the main app.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-side" id="status">
      <aside class="note">
        <h2>Initial scope</h2>
        <p>
          This repo is set up only for the static site foundation. Content,
          structure, CMS decisions, and launch design can be handled next.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Single Astro page scaffold</li>
          <li>Basic brand image and favicon set</li>
          <li>Ready for Netlify and GitHub wiring</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>

      <aside class="note">
        <h2>Intended topology</h2>
        <p>
          The marketing site will live separately from the product surfaces.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>iotera.asia</strong> for the lander</li>
          <li><strong>app.iotera.asia</strong> for the product UI</li>
          <li><strong>api.iotera.asia</strong> for the backend API</li>
          <li><strong>mqtt.iotera.asia</strong> for broker access</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <p class="footer">
    Barebones starter page. Replace this once the content model and launch
    direction are decided.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
